{"title_page": "Thor Halvorssen (human rights activist)", "text_new": "{{short description|Venezuelan human rights activist}}\n{{for|Halvorssen's father|Thor Halvorssen Hellum}}\n{{Spanish name|first=Halvorssen|second=Mendoza}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               =  Thor Halvorssen Mendoza\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| alt                = \n| image = Thor Halvorssen.jpg\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         =  Thor Leonardo Halvorssen Mendoza\n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|1976|03|09}}<ref name=NYT07/><ref name=\"Forbes 2010\" />\n| birth_place        = [[Venezuela]]\n| baptised           =  <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered -->\n| disappeared_date   =  <!-- {{disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date then birth date) -->\n| disappeared_place  = \n| disappeared_status = \n| death_date         =  <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| body_discovered    = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| ethnicity          =  <!-- Ethnicity should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| citizenship        = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Pennsylvania]]\n| occupation         = \n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = [[Human Rights Foundation]] {{small|(Founder and CEO)}}<br>[[Oslo Freedom Forum]] {{small|(Founder)}}\n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          =  <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             =  <!-- {{height|cm=X}} OR {{height|ft=X|in=Y}}-->\n| weight             =  <!-- {{convert|X|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} or {{convert|X|lb|kg|0|abbr=on}} -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| religion           =  <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| denomination       =  <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| criminal_charge    =  <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = \n| partner            =  <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| website            =  <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| footnotes          = \n| box_width          = \n}}\n'''Thor Leonardo Halvorssen Mendoza''' (born 1976<ref name=NYT07/><ref name=\"Forbes 2010\">{{cite news | title = Revaluing Freedom: Oslo Forum aims to become the Davos of human rights | url = https://www.forbes.com/2010/05/07/oslo-forum-human-rights-united-nations-opinions-columnists-claudia-rosett.html | work = [[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]] | first = Claudia | last = Rosett | date= May 7, 2010}}</ref>)\u2014commonly known as '''Thor Halvorssen''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8to\u027e al.\u02c8\u03b2o\u027es.s\u025b\u0303n}}){{ref label|FullName|a|a}}\u2014is a [[Venezuela]]n human rights advocate and film producer with contributions in the field of public policy, public interest advocacy, individual rights and civil liberties, and pro-democracy advocacy. ''[[The New York Times]]'' described Halvorssen as a maverick \"who champions the underdog and the powerless.\"<ref name=NYT07/> Buzzfeed publishes that Halvorssen \"possesses a burning desire to right the countless injustices of this world and he has committed himself to this task with an intensity to match that of the dictatorship he has placed in his sights.  And he does not care if those injustices are being committed by the 'right-wing' or 'left-wing' regimes.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gray|first1=Rosie|title=Is This The Face Of A New Global Human Rights Movement?|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/rosiegray/is-this-the-face-of-a-new-global-human-rights-movement#.bixEVNWgK|website=buzzfeed.com|publisher=Buzzfeed, Inc.|date=2013}}</ref>\n\nHalvorssen is founder of the [[Oslo Freedom Forum]], an annual gathering described by ''[[The Economist]]'' as a \"spectacular human-rights festival&nbsp;... on its way to becoming a human-rights equivalent of the Davos economic forum\".<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.economist.com/world/international/displaystory.cfm?story_id=16219707 | work=The Economist | title=A crowded field | date=May 27, 2010}}</ref> Halvorssen is president of the [[Human Rights Foundation]], an organization devoted to global human rights and freedom.  He is the Patron of the Czech-based Children's Peace Movement, On Own Feet,<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/a-different-kind-of-army_b_574450.html | work=[[Huffington Post]] | first=Thor | last=Halvorssen | title=A Different Kind of Army | date=April 26, 2011}}</ref>\nHalvorssen bought the traditionally leftist Norwegian news magazine ''[[Ny Tid]]'' in May 2010.<ref name=\"Ny Tid\">{{cite news | url=http://www.nytid.no/nyheter/artikler/20100510/ny-tid-far-internasjonale-eiere/ | title=Global Solidarity in Action: New owners of Ny Tid | work=[[Ny Tid]] | date=May 10, 2010 | accessdate=June 3, 2016| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100906132511/http://www.nytid.no/nyheter/artikler/20100510/ny-tid-far-internasjonale-eiere/ | archivedate=September 6, 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHalvorssen's opinions have appeared in ''[[The New York Times]]'', ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', ''[[The Washington Post]]'', [[National Public Radio]], [[Time (magazine)|''Time'' magazine]], ''[[The Nation]]'' and ''[[National Journal]]'', and he has appeared on television outlets such as [[al-Jazeera]], [[BBC News]],<ref>{{cite press release |author=The Human Rights Foundation |url=http://humanrightsfoundation.org/news/hrf-on-bbc-world-news-tv-today-to-discuss-north-korea-balloon-launch-00349 |title=HRF on BBC World News TV Today to Discuss North Korea Balloon Launch &#124; News |publisher=The Human Rights Foundation |date=2014-01-22 |accessdate=2014-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505081553/http://humanrightsfoundation.org/news/hrf-on-bbc-world-news-tv-today-to-discuss-north-korea-balloon-launch-00349 |archive-date=2014-05-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> [[Fox News Channel]]\u2019s ''[[The O'Reilly Factor]]'' and ''[[Hannity & Colmes]]'', [[MSNBC]]\u2019s ''[[Hardball with Chris Matthews]]'', [[CNN]], and [[HBO]]. Thor Halvorssen was a speaker at [[TED (conference)|TEDx]] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]] in October 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thedp.com/article/tedxpenn-exceeded-expectations |title=TEDxPenn exceeded expectations |publisher=Thedp.com |date=2010-10-04 |accessdate=2014-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110518135620/http://thedp.com/article/tedxpenn-exceeded-expectations |archive-date=2011-05-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nHalvorssen testified to the U.S. Congress that he was the target of a smear campaign by [[Fusion GPS]]. Halvorssen provided testimony to the U.S. Senate Judiciary Committee in July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Halvorssen|first1=Thor|title=Here is my testimony to U.S. @senjudiciary committee about paid smear campaigns of #FusionGPS #Derwick #Venezuela \u2026|url=https://twitter.com/ThorHalvorssen/status/889989736718254080|website=twitter.com|accessdate=29 July 2017|date=25 July 2017|quote=https://www.scribd.com/document/354721041/Testimony-of-Thor-Halvorssen-to-the-Senate-Committee-on-the-Judiciary-7-26-2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Lee|title='Fusion GPS' Sleazy Venezuela Links Shed New Light on Trump Dossier|url=http://www.tabletmag.com/jewish-news-and-politics/241812/news-for-hire-scandal-deepens-gps-fusion-sleazy-venezuela-links-shed-new-light-on-trump-dossier|website=tabletmag.com|publisher=Tablet Magazine|accessdate=29 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nHalvorssen was born in Venezuela to Hilda Mendoza, a descendant and a relative, respectively, of Venezuela's first president [[Crist\u00f3bal Mendoza]] and liberator [[Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar]]. His father is [[Thor Halvorssen Hellum]], who served as a Venezuelan Ambassador for anti-Narcotic Affairs in the administration of [[Carlos Andr\u00e9s P\u00e9rez]] and as special overseas investigator of a Venezuelan Senate Commission. His family was prosperous and on his father's side he is the grandson of \u00d8ystein Halvorssen, who served as Norway's [[Consul (representative)|honorary consul-general]] in [[Caracas]]<ref>''[[Aftenposten]]'', 26 August 1947, p. 5</ref> and who \"built a family dynasty as the Venezuelan representative for corporations including [[Dunlop Rubber|Dunlop]], [[Alfa Laval]] and [[Ericsson]].\"<ref name=NYT07>[[Strausbaugh, John]] (August 19, 2007). [https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/19/movies/19stra.html \"A Maverick Mogul, Proudly Politically Incorrect\"].  ''[[New York Times]]''. (Archived by [[WebCite]] [https://web.archive.org/web/20110511214626/http://www.nytimes.com:80/2007/08/19/movies/19stra.html? here.])</ref> His cousin is [[Leopoldo Lopez]].<ref>Halvorssen, Thor (March 14, 2012). [http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/opinion/perspectives/hugo-chavez-channels-the-dead-259423/?print=1 \"Hugo Chavez channels the dead\".] ''Pittsburgh Post Gazette''</ref> a Venezuelan politician, activist, and a political prisoner after called for peaceful protests in February 2014.\n\nHalvorssen attended the [[University of Pennsylvania]] and graduated [[Phi Beta Kappa]] and [[magna cum laude]], with concurrent undergraduate and graduate degrees in Political Science and History.\n\n===Father's imprisonment===\nHalvorssen\u2019s father, also named [[Thor Halvorssen (businessman)|Thor Halvorssen,]] was a wealthy businessman who was named the CEO of Venezuela's state TV CANTV<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cantv.com.ve/Portales/Cantv/Data/CANTVINF06/06_presidentes.asp|title=Can TV Past Presidents|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>. In 1989, then-President Carlos Andres Perez appointed Halvorssen Sr. as Venezuela\u2019s \u201canti-drug ambassador.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qaS0CwAAQBAJ&lpg=PA139&ots=CWu0sIyA-N&dq=Those%20Halvorssen%20anti%20drug%20tzar&pg=PA139#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Drug Politics: Dirty Money and Democracies|last=Jordan|first=David C.|date=2016-01-22|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press|year=|isbn=978-0-8061-7221-7|location=|pages=139|language=en}}</ref>\u201d \n\nWhen Halvorssen was a freshman at the University of Pennsylvania,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Grady |first1=Rosie |title=Is This The Face Of A New Global Human Rights Movement? |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/rosiegray/is-this-the-face-of-a-new-global-human-rights-movement |publisher=Buzzfeed News |accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref> in 1993, his father was arrested while investigating the [[Medell\u00edn cartel]] for [[money laundering]] and [[bank fraud]]. His father was tortured, beaten, and in danger of being murdered<ref name=\"foes\" /> during his 74-day incarceration in a Caracas jail on \"trumped-up\" charges of terrorism.<ref name=\"Hilton\">[[Isabel Hilton|Hilton, Isabel]]. \"Presumed Guilty\".  ''[[Gentlemen's Quarterly]] (GQ)'' UK: July 1994.</ref><ref name=\"Fonzi\">Fonzi, Gaeton. \"The Troublemaker\". ''[[The Pennsylvania Gazette]]'' (November 1994)</ref><ref name=\"talcual20010829\">{{cite web|url=http://www.talcualdigital.com/ediciones/2001/08/29/p9s1.htm|title=Recuerdos del terrorismo caraque\u00f1o|accessdate=March 3, 2007|publisher=[[Tal Cual]]|date=August 29, 2001|first=Manuel|last=Malaver |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20040823191004/http://www.talcualdigital.com/ediciones/2001/08/29/p9s1.htm |archivedate = August 23, 2004|language=es}}</ref> Halvorssen led the campaign for his father\u2019s release, garnering help from [[Amnesty International]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Grady |first1=Rosie |title=Is This The Face Of A New Global Human Rights Movement? |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/rosiegray/is-this-the-face-of-a-new-global-human-rights-movement |publisher=Buzzfeed News |accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref> which issued protests along with other International organizations. Halvorssen was eventually found not guilty of all charges. After his release the [[United Nations]]-affiliated [[International Society for Human Rights]] appointed him director of their Pan-American Committee.<ref name=\"foes\">[http://www.csmonitor.com/1993/1220/20012.html Venezuelan Anti-Drug Official Fights His Foes From a Prison Cell:] Evidence suggests Thor Halvorssen was framed by Colombian drug lords and their Caracas `friends'; ''[[Christian Science Monitor]]''. Boston, Mass.: Dec 20, 1993.</ref><ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/1993/1224/24102.html Former Venezuelan Drug Official Freed;] ''Christian Science Monitor''. Boston, Mass.: Dec 24, 1993.</ref><ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  The Americas: The price of vigilance in Venezuela's banking community. ''[[Wall Street Journal]]''. New York, N.Y.: Mar 4, 1994. pg. A9 [http://oilwars.blogspot.com/2005/06/good-old-days-iii.html Available online here.]</ref>\n\n===Mother's shooting===\nWhile attending a peaceful protest of the [[Venezuelan recall referendum of 2004]], Halvorssen's mother, Hilda Mendoza Denham, a British subject, was shot.<ref>[http://www.eursoc.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/593/Briton_Shot_In_Venezuela.html Briton Shot In Venezuela.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928202339/http://www.eursoc.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/593/Briton_Shot_In_Venezuela.html |date=2007-09-28 }} EURSOC, (August 19, 2004).  Retrieved on September 14, 2006.</ref>  Images of government supporters firing upon the demonstrators were captured by a live television broadcast.<ref name=OtraVez>{{in lang|es}} Olivares, Francisco. [http://archivo.eluniversal.com/2004/09/05/pol_art_05154A.shtml Otra vez los pistoleros.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710184947/http://archivo.eluniversal.com/2004/09/05/pol_art_05154A.shtml |date=2011-07-10 }} ''[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]'' (5 September 2004).  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref><ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://urru.org/fotos/0_2004/20040816_NuevaMasacreAltamira.htm Fotos de la nueva masacre de Altamira, 2004.08.16] urru.org. Retrieved on September 14, 2006.</ref>  ''[[Wall Street Journal|The Wall Street Journal]]'' published an article written by Halvorssen about the shooting of his mother by members of the Venezuelan government security apparatus.<ref>Halvorssen, Thor L. The Price of Dissent in Venezuela.  ''Wall Street Journal'' (Eastern edition), Aug 19, 2004. p. A.12 Discussed online [https://web.archive.org/web/20041212014551/http://www.newsmax.com/archives/articles/2004/8/20/131240.shtml here.]</ref> The gunmen were later apprehended, tried, had their sentences revoked, tried again, found guilty, and received 3-year sentences for murder and for bodily harm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://merida.tsj.gov.ve/decisiones/2007/agosto/1812-22-359-06-.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-08-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110821193753/http://merida.tsj.gov.ve/decisiones/2007/agosto/1812-22-359-06-.html |archivedate=2011-08-21 }}</ref><ref>[http://mensual.prensa.com/mensual/contenido/2006/04/11/hoy/mundo/563578.html Revocan condena a \u2018pistoleros de Altamira\u2019.] ''Prensa.com'' (11 April 2006)</ref> They were released after serving six months in prison.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Arenas|first1=Macky|title=El ABC de Katty Ron / Hermana de Maritza Ron, asesinada en Plaza Altamira \"Mi hermana vino a votar para el Revocatorio, sin imaginar que encontrar\u00eda la muerte\"|url=http://www.abcdelasemana.com/2014/07/24/el-abc-de-katty-ron-hermana-de-maritza-ron-asesinada-en-plaza-altamirami-hermana-vino-a-votar-para-el-revocatorio-sin-imaginar-que-encontraria-la-muerte/|website=abcdelasemana.com|publisher=ABC de la Semana|date=2014}}</ref>\n\n==Activism==\nHalvorssen has a specialty on matters regarding dictatorships, [[human trafficking]], slavery, and threats to democracy. He has lectured widely on the subject of human rights including at [[Harvard Law School]], the New York City Junto, the [[United Nations Association]] in New York, and the [[American Enterprise Institute]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hclaweb.org/conference/panels-speakers/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-06-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621040821/http://hclaweb.org/conference/panels-speakers/ |archivedate=2010-06-21 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nycjunto.com/library/2007/05/Halvorssen.htm |title=The New York City Junto |website=Nycjunto.com |date=2007-05-03 |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unanyc.org/events/archive/2008/20080320_halvorssen.html |title=UNA-NY: Event Archive |website=Unanyc.org |date=2008-03-20 |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aei.org/event/1439 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-06-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100531083028/http://www.aei.org/event/1439 |archivedate=2010-05-31 }}</ref> Halvorssen has also spoken at the British parliament.<ref name=TRTP>{{cite web|title=The Responsibility to Protect|url=http://henryjacksonsociety.org/2011/11/08/the-responsibility-to-protect/|publisher=The Henry Jackson Society|accessdate=3 May 2012}}</ref>.\n\n===Lucent Technologies===\nIn 1999, Halvorssen spearheaded a campaign on the floor of the [[Lucent|Lucent Technologies]] annual shareholder meeting appealing for the creation of an anti-slave labor policy whereby Lucent would require China to certify that Lucent's products were not fabricated using [[slave labor]].  China's [[Laogai]] camps allegedly imprison eight million men, women, and children in 1100 factories, farms, and other facilities producing a wide range of consumer products.<ref>[http://www.newstrolls.com/news/dev/guest/022299.htm Lucent Stockowners Want Anti-Slave Labor Policy for China Operations.] Retrieved on August 26, 2006. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051215010656/http://www.newstrolls.com/news/dev/guest/022299.htm |date=December 15, 2005 }}</ref>\n\n===Foundation for Individual Rights in Education===\nIn 1999, Halvorssen became the first executive director and chief executive officer of the [[Foundation for Individual Rights in Education]] (FIRE), a U.S. civil liberties organization. As head of FIRE, Halvorssen formed coalitions that brought together the conservative and libertarian advocacy organizations such as the [[Heritage Foundation]], Feminists for Free Expression, the [[Eagle Forum]], with more traditional free speech defenders such as the [[ACLU]].  Halvorssen has a track record of defending individuals both on the right<ref>[[William F. Buckley|Buckley, William F. Jr.]]  [http://www.nationalreview.com/buckley/buckleyprint041001.html Who Do We Blame?  The case of a YAF student chapter at Penn State.] ''[[National Review]]'' (April 10, 2001).  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> and on the left of the political spectrum.<ref>Carlson, Scott.  [http://chronicle.com/free/2002/09/2002092703t.htm University Orders Student Group to Remove Online Link to a Rebel Group's Web Site.]  ''[[The Chronicle of Higher Education]]'' (September 27, 2002). Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref>\n\nIn 2001, Halvorssen stated that, \"Liberty of opinion, speech, and expression is indispensable to a free and, in the deepest sense, progressive society. Deny it to one, and you deny it effectively to all. These truths long have been ignored and betrayed on our campuses, to the peril of a free society.\"<ref>Halvorssen, Thor L. [http://www.boundless.org/2001/departments/campus_culture/a0000505.html Campus Tyranny.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050318051352/http://www.boundless.org/2001/departments/campus_culture/a0000505.html |date=2005-03-18 }} Retrieved on August 26, 2006.</ref>  In a 2003 moderated chat, he said, \"History has taught us that a society that does not respect individual rights, freedom of conscience, and freedom of speech will not long survive as a free society in any form.\"<ref>[http://chronicle.com/colloquylive/2003/04/speech/ Tests for Academic Freedom in a Time of War.]  ''The Chronicle of Higher Education''. (April 17, 2003). Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref>\n\n===Human Rights Foundation===\nHalvorssen stepped down as head of FIRE in March 2004 to join its Board of Advisors and announced the creation of an international group that would \"champion the definition of human rights that originally animated the human rights movement, centered on the twin concepts of freedom of self-determination and freedom from tyranny.\"<ref name=dartreview>Glabe, Scott L. [http://dartreview.com/archives/2005/11/22/new_organization_opens_fire_on_chavez.php New Organization Opens Fire on Chavez] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081120103351/http://dartreview.com/archives/2005/11/22/new_organization_opens_fire_on_chavez.php |date=November 20, 2008 }}, ''[[The Dartmouth Review]]'', November 22, 2005. Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> HRF was incorporated in 2005, opening its headquarters in [[New York City]] in August 2006. Its International Council includes several well-known prisoners of conscience such as [[Elie Wiesel]], [[Harry Wu]], and [[Vladimir Bukovsky]]. It also includes democracy activists such as [[Mart Laar]], and [[Garry Kasparov]]. Its chairman until his death in December 2011, was [[V\u00e1clav Havel]].\n\nAt the helm of HRF Halvorssen has repeatedly lobbied and advocated for the release of Chinese political prisoner [[Liu Xiaobo]].<ref name=\"HR Big Winner\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=Human Rights Is Big Winner in Nobel Peace Prize Selection|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/human-rights-is-big-winne_b_756042.html|accessdate=3 May 2012|newspaper=The Huffington Post|date=October 8, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Truth Outweigh\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=Truth will Outweigh the Chinese Dictatorship--Liu Xiaobo's Freedom is the Test|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/truth-will-outweigh-the-c_b_800537.html|accessdate=3 May 2012|newspaper=The Huffington Post|date=December 23, 2010}}</ref>  In 2010 Halvorssen was special guest of Liu Xiaobo at the Nobel Prize ceremony awarding the prize to Liu Xiaobo in absentia.<ref name=\"HRF Support\">{{cite web|title=HRF announces its membership in the International Committee to Support Liu Xiaobo|url=http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/media/HRFannouncesitsmembershipintheInternationalCommitteetoSupportLiuXiaobo12092011.html|publisher=Human Rights Foundation|accessdate=3 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310181103/http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/media/HRFannouncesitsmembershipintheInternationalCommitteetoSupportLiuXiaobo12092011.html|archive-date=10 March 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"NPP Winners\">{{cite news|title=Nobel Peace Prize winners campaign to release Chinese dissident Liu Xiaobo|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/8945006/Nobel-Peace-Prize-winners-campaign-to-release-Chinese-dissident-Liu-Xiaobo.html|publisher=The Telegraph|accessdate=3 May 2012|location=London|date=December 9, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Winners Urge\">{{cite news|title=Nobel winners urge China to release Liu Xiaobo|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/feedarticle/9987302|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=3 May 2012|location=London|date=January 23, 2008}}</ref> Halvorssen is identified as a supporter of Chinese [[Uyghur people|Uyghur]] leader [[Rebiya Kadeer]] and has sharply criticized the Tawainese [[Kuomintang]] government for its banning visits by Kadeer.<ref name=\"Fails to Learn\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=Taiwan Fails to Learn From Its Own History|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/taiwan-fails-to-learn-fro_1_b_684936.html|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=3 May 2012|date=August 17, 2010}}</ref> Halvorssen has supported UN-level action to address the violations of Uyghur rights in China.\n\nHalvorssen appears as a frequent critic of [[Uganda]]\u2019s president [[Yoweri Museveni]] and, in particular, the legislative efforts in Uganda to punish [[homosexuality]] with the death penalty.<ref name=\"UN Okay\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=United Nations: It's Okay to Kill the Gay|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/united-nations-its-okay-t_b_787024.html|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=3 May 2012|date=November 23, 2010}}</ref>\nHalvorssen is a critic of [[Hugo Ch\u00e1vez]],<ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/005/177yckaw.asp Guerrilla Nation.]  ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' (January 26, 2005).</ref> and has written on Venezuela\u2019s [[anti-Semitism]] and the assault on democracy and individual rights in [[Latin America]].<ref name=Hurricane>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/005/903jhsjt.asp?pg=1 Hurricane Hugo.]  ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'', August 8, 2005, Volume 010, Issue 44.  Also available at [http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0RMQ/is_44_10/ai_n14895831/print LookSmart.]</ref> Halvorssen's criticisms have also been directed at U.S. Republicans such as [[Jack Kemp]]<ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/002/785ruylo.asp?pg=2 Hugo Chavez vs. the Media.] ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' (June 9, 2003).</ref> as well as Democrats including [[John Conyers]] and [[Jos\u00e9 Enrique Serrano|Jose Serrano]].<ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/002/346jorji.asp Comandante Chavez's Friends.]  ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' (March 11, 2003).</ref> In a symposium published by the American conservative magazine ''[[National Review]]'', he condemned [[Augusto Pinochet]] for his human rights abuses.<ref>Halvorssen, Thor (December 11, 2006). [https://archive.is/20120527052919/http://article.nationalreview.com/300658/pinochet-is-history/nro-symposium Pinochet Is History.] National Review Online Symposium.  Retrieved on February 21, 2010.</ref><ref>Knapp, Alex (December 13, 2006). [http://www.outsidethebeltway.com/archives/another_symposium_of_denial/ Another Symposium of Denial.] Outside the Beltway. Retrieved on February 21, 2010.</ref> Halvorssen led a campaign to expose [[Chechnya|Chechen]] president [[Ramzan Kadyrov]]\u2019s human rights violations and ultimately created a firestorm for Hollywood actress [[Hilary Swank]] after she accepted a cash payment to celebrate Kadyrov\u2019s birthday.<ref name=\"Party Criticism\">{{cite news|title=Hilary Swank under fire for attending Ramzan Kadyrov's party in Chechnya|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/oct/11/hilary-swank-ramzan-kadyrov-chechnya|accessdate=3 May 2012|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|first=Ben|last=Child|date=October 11, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"PR Disaster\">{{cite news|title=Hilary Swank sacks manager and staff following Ramzan Kadyrov PR disaster|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/oct/31/hilary-swank-sacks-manager|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=3 May 2012|location=London|first=Ben|last=Child|date=October 31, 2011}}</ref>  In the same manner Halvorssen has exposed payments from dictators to [[Jennifer Lopez]], [[Erykah Baduh]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[Nelly Furtado]], and [[50 Cent]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Daunt|first1=Tina|title=Jennifer Lopez Accused of Accepting $10 Million From 'Dictators and Crooks'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennifer-lopez-accused-accepting-10-584679 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Human Rights Group Slams Mariah Carey for Concert in Angola|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/human-rights-group-slams-mariah-666951|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Halvorssen|first1=Thor|last2=Gladstein|first2=Alex|title=Erykah Badu\u2019s Oppressively Apolitical Stance on Human Rights|url=http://time.com/85126/erykah-badu-swaziland-human-rights/|website=time.com|publisher=Time|date=2014}}</ref>\n\nOther advocacy campaigns include [[Panama]]\u2019s president [[Ricardo Martinelli]] on freedom of speech violations; political prisoner cases in [[Venezuela]], [[Vietnam]], [[Cuba]], and [[Bolivia]]; as well as the rights of human rights defenders in [[Colombia]].\n\n===Oslo Freedom Forum===\n{{main|Oslo Freedom Forum}}\nIn 2009, Halvorssen founded a global gathering of human rights advocates called the Oslo Freedom Forum. It has taken place in Oslo annually since then.  According to ''[[Wired Magazine]]'', \"if the global human-rights movement were to create its own unified representative body, it would look something like this.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rowan|first1=David|title=Oslo Freedom Forum brings together the global human rights movement|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2012-05/14/30-things-i-learned-at-the-oslo-freedom-forum|website=[[Wired Magazine]]|publisher=Conde Nast UK|date=2014|access-date=2017-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160419092201/http://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2012-05/14/30-things-i-learned-at-the-oslo-freedom-forum|archive-date=2016-04-19|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nNorwegian newspaper ''[[Verdens Gang]]'' called it a \"Gathering of Heroes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hanneskartveit.vgb.no/2010/05/28/heltene-samles-i-oslo/ |title=Heltene samles i Oslo |publisher=Hanne Skartveit |date=2010-05-28 |accessdate=2014-05-24 |language=no |trans-title=The heroes gather in Oslo}}</ref>  ''[[The Economist]]'' calls it the \"Davos of Human Rights.\" Participants include [[Pussy Riot]]'s [[Nadezhda Tolokonnikova]] and [[Maria Aliokhina]], Sudan's [[Lubna al-Hussein]], Burma's [[Aung San Suu Kyi]], China's [[Ai Weiwei]], Tahrir Square protest organizer [[Wael Ghonim]], Wikipedia founder [[Jimmy Wales]], Holocaust survivor [[Elie Wiesel]], Iran's [[Marina Nemat]], [[Peter Thiel]], [[Julian Assange]], [[V\u00e1clav Havel]], [[Garry Kasparov]], [[Leopoldo Lopez]], Nobel laureate [[Lech Walesa]], and Russian political prisoner [[Mikhail Khodorkovskii]].\n\n===Children's Peace Movement===\nSince 2009, Halvorssen is listed as \"Patron\" of the Children's Peace Movement, On Own Feet.  Known as the \"Centipede Movement\" it is a Czech-based group that facilitates bilateral relations between children and adolescents in [[Poland]], the [[Czech Republic]], [[Slovakia]], [[Canada]], and [[Norway]] with children in war-torn countries such as [[Afghanistan]] and [[Iraq]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/a-different-kind-of-army_b_574450.html |title=A Different Kind of Army |publisher=[[The Huffington Post]] |date= |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.stonozka.org/ |title=Hnut\u00ed Na vlastn\u00edch nohou - Stono\u017eka |website=Stonozka.org |date= |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref> The previous Patron was former Czech president [[V\u00e1clav Havel]].\n\n==Film==\nHalvorssen executive produced ''Hammer & Tickle'', a film about the power of humor, ridicule, and satire as the language of truth under Soviet tyranny. This film premiered at Tribeca in 2006.<ref name=\"IMDb\" /> The film won Best New Documentary Film at the [[Zurich Film Festival]].<ref>[http://www.zurichfilmfestival.org/en/welcome/detail/article/81/4/ Closing Night of the 2nd Zurich Film Festival.]{{dead link|date=January 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}} [[Zurich Film Festival]] (October 10, 2006).  Retrieved on December 9, 2006.</ref>\n\nHalvorssen co-produced the film ''Freedom's Fury'' which was executive produced by [[Lucy Liu]], [[Quentin Tarantino]], and [[Andrew Vajna]]. It premiered at the [[Tribeca Film Festival]].<ref name=\"IMDb\">{{IMDb name|id=1812816}} Retrieved on August 26, 2006.</ref><ref>Cold War Tale Told at Last. ''[[New York Post]]'' (April 29, 2006). [http://pqarchiver.nypost.com/nypost/access/1029793191.html?dids=1029793191:1029793191&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Apr+29%2C+2006&author=&pub=New+York+Post&edition=&startpage=011&desc=COLD+WAR+TALE+TOLD+AT+LAST Available online.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714220157/http://pqarchiver.nypost.com/nypost/access/1029793191.html?dids=1029793191:1029793191&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Apr+29,+2006&author=&pub=New+York+Post&edition=&startpage=011&desc=COLD+WAR+TALE+TOLD+AT+LAST |date=2011-07-14 }}</ref> The film relates the story of the [[Hungarian Revolution of 1956|uprising against the government that occurred in Hungary]] in 1956.\n\nHalvorssen is producer of the film ''The Singing Revolution'', a film about [[Estonia]]'s peaceful struggle for political independence from [[Occupation of the Baltic states|Soviet occupation]].<ref name=SR>[http://www.singingrevolution.com/cgi-local/content.cgi?pg=1&p=3 The Singing Revolution.] Official website.  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> The film premiered at the [[Black Nights Film Festival]] in December 2006 where it received a 15-minute standing ovation.<ref>[http://www.singingrevolution.com/cgi-local/reviews.cgi Reviews.] The Singing Revolution.  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> Since then, it has become the most successful documentary film in Estonian box-office history.<ref>[http://www.estosite.org/home/?page_id=23 Singing Revolution.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100212123502/http://www.estosite.org/home/?page_id=23 |date=2010-02-12 }} Estosite.org.  Retrieved on February 21, 2010.</ref>\n\nHalvorssen produced ''The Dissident'' in 2019, a film about the murder of Saudi journalist [[Jamal Khashoggi]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Glieberman |first1=Owen |title=\u2018The Dissident\u2019: Film Review |url=\u2018The Dissident\u2019: Film Review |publisher=Variety |accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref> The film was directed by Academy-Award winning director [[Bryan Fogel]]. [https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/dissident-review-1272803]\n\n===Filmography===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Thor Halvorssen's Filmography<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1812816/|title=Thor Halvorssen|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n!Title \n!Year \n!Role \n|-\n|Hammer & Tickle \n|2006\n|Producer\n|-\n|Freedom's Fury \n|2006\n|Producer\n|-\n|The Singing Revolution\n|2006\n|Producer\n|-\n|The Sugar Babies\n|2007\n|Producer\n|-\n|Indoctrinate U \n|2007\n|Producer\n|-\n|2081 \n|2009\n|Producer\n|-\n|Pups of Liberty\n|2009\n|Executive Producer\n|-\n|U.N. Me \n|2009\n|Executive Producer\n|-\n|State of Control\n|2016\n|Producer\n|-\n|The Dissident \n|2020\n|Producer\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nUniversity of Pennsylvania president [[Judith Rodin]] honored Halvorssen's achievements by awarding him the Sol Feinstone Award for protecting student speech.<ref>[http://www.publiceye.org/ifas/cnp/bios/halth.html Thor Halvorssen.]  PublicEye.org Retrieved 26 August 2006.</ref>\n\nIn 2010 Romanian leader [[Emil Constantinescu]] presented Halvorssen with a presidential silver medal to commemorate the tenth anniversary of the [[Romanian Revolution of 1989]]. \"On behalf of those who fought and died for freedom, I present this medal to the Oslo Freedom Forum founder, and remind those here that even if Romanians live in democracy now, we cannot feel entirely free as long as other people \u2013 who live under dictatorial and repressive regimes anywhere in the world \u2013 are not also be free.\"<ref>[http://thehrf.org/media/042910.html ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728094549/http://thehrf.org/media/042910.html |date=July 28, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Halvorssen was awarded the Millennium Candler Justice Prize, honoring leadership in effecting positive social change, presented at the [[Millennium Gate Museum]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thegatemuseum.org/gala-2018-millennium-candler-honorees/|title=Millennium Gate Museum {{!}}   2018 Millennium Candler Honorees|website=thegatemuseum.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-26}}</ref> The prize was previously awarded to Former First Lady Rosalynn Carter and to Prince Jean of Orl\u00e9ans, Dauphin of France.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mdjonline.com/neighbor_newspapers/northside_sandy_springs/community/national-monuments-foundation-sends-delegation-to-denmark-announces-awards/article_e8a2fde0-a228-11e7-a7e9-f30ea43f0159.html|title=National Monuments Foundation sends delegation to Denmark, announces 2018 awards|last=Staff|first=Neighbor|work=MDJOnline.com|access-date=2018-10-26|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\n* Halvorssen, Thor L (1996). [https://books.google.com/books?id=HLSjNwAACAAJ&dq=thor+halvorssen ''Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar and the Enlightenment''], University of Pennsylvania.\n\n== Notes ==\n:{{note label|FullName|a|a}} Halvorssen Mendoza is known commonly as Thor Halvorssen.  Per Venezuelan naming conventions, his full legal name includes both his father's (Halvorssen) and mother's (Mendoza) surnames. His full, legal, Venezuelan name distinguishes him from his father, [[Thor Halvorssen Hellum]]. (See [https://web.archive.org/web/20070706171607/http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/es/thor-es.html Thor Halvorssen - Presidente.] The Human Rights Foundation.  Retrieved on July 21, 2007. {{in lang|es}} Also see [https://archive.is/20130415000554/http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/reports/hcletter.html re: Francisco Us\u00f3n\u2014Political Prisoner and Prisoner of Conscience.]  Human Rights Foundation.  Retrieved on July 21, 2007.)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Twitter|ThorHalvorssen}}\n* {{Facebook page|thorhalvorssen}}\n* [https://www.theatlantic.com/author/thor-halvorssen/ ''The Atlantic'' profile]\n* [https://www.huffpost.com/author/thor-halvorssen ''HuffPost'' profile]\n* {{IMDb name|1812816}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Halvorssen Mendoza, Thor}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American democracy activists]]\n[[Category:American film producers]]\n[[Category:American human rights activists]]\n[[Category:HuffPost writers and columnists]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan human rights activists]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan people of Norwegian descent]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan expatriates in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Venezuelan human rights activist}}\n{{for|Halvorssen's father|Thor Halvorssen Hellum}}\n{{Spanish name|first=Halvorssen|second=Mendoza}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               =  Thor Halvorssen Mendoza\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| alt                = \n| image = Thor Halvorssen.jpg\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         =  Thor Leonardo Halvorssen Mendoza\n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|1976|03|09}}<ref name=NYT07/><ref name=\"Forbes 2010\" />\n| birth_place        = [[Venezuela]]\n| baptised           =  <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered -->\n| disappeared_date   =  <!-- {{disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date then birth date) -->\n| disappeared_place  = \n| disappeared_status = \n| death_date         =  <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| body_discovered    = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| ethnicity          =  <!-- Ethnicity should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| citizenship        = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Pennsylvania]]\n| occupation         = \n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = [[Human Rights Foundation]] {{small|(Founder and CEO)}}<br>[[Oslo Freedom Forum]] {{small|(Founder)}}\n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          =  <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             =  <!-- {{height|cm=X}} OR {{height|ft=X|in=Y}}-->\n| weight             =  <!-- {{convert|X|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} or {{convert|X|lb|kg|0|abbr=on}} -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| religion           =  <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| denomination       =  <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| criminal_charge    =  <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = \n| partner            =  <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| module3            = \n| module4            = \n| module5            = \n| module6            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| website            =  <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| footnotes          = \n| box_width          = \n}}\n'''Thor Leonardo Halvorssen Mendoza''' (born 1976<ref name=NYT07/><ref name=\"Forbes 2010\">{{cite news | title = Revaluing Freedom: Oslo Forum aims to become the Davos of human rights | url = https://www.forbes.com/2010/05/07/oslo-forum-human-rights-united-nations-opinions-columnists-claudia-rosett.html | work = [[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]] | first = Claudia | last = Rosett | date= May 7, 2010}}</ref>)\u2014commonly known as '''Thor Halvorssen''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8to\u027e al.\u02c8\u03b2o\u027es.s\u025b\u0303n}}){{ref label|FullName|a|a}}\u2014is a [[Venezuela]]n human rights advocate and film producer with contributions in the field of public policy, public interest advocacy, individual rights and civil liberties, and pro-democracy advocacy. ''[[The New York Times]]'' described Halvorssen as a maverick \"who champions the underdog and the powerless.\"<ref name=NYT07/> Buzzfeed publishes that Halvorssen \"possesses a burning desire to right the countless injustices of this world and he has committed himself to this task with an intensity to match that of the dictatorship he has placed in his sights.  And he does not care if those injustices are being committed by the 'right-wing' or 'left-wing' regimes.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gray|first1=Rosie|title=Is This The Face Of A New Global Human Rights Movement?|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/rosiegray/is-this-the-face-of-a-new-global-human-rights-movement#.bixEVNWgK|website=buzzfeed.com|publisher=Buzzfeed, Inc.|date=2013}}</ref>\n\nHalvorssen is founder of the [[Oslo Freedom Forum]], an annual gathering described by ''[[The Economist]]'' as a \"spectacular human-rights festival&nbsp;... on its way to becoming a human-rights equivalent of the Davos economic forum\".<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.economist.com/world/international/displaystory.cfm?story_id=16219707 | work=The Economist | title=A crowded field | date=May 27, 2010}}</ref> Halvorssen is president of the [[Human Rights Foundation]], an organization devoted to global human rights and freedom.  He is the Patron of the Czech-based Children's Peace Movement, On Own Feet,<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/a-different-kind-of-army_b_574450.html | work=[[Huffington Post]] | first=Thor | last=Halvorssen | title=A Different Kind of Army | date=April 26, 2011}}</ref>\nHalvorssen bought the traditionally leftist Norwegian news magazine ''[[Ny Tid]]'' in May 2010.<ref name=\"Ny Tid\">{{cite news | url=http://www.nytid.no/nyheter/artikler/20100510/ny-tid-far-internasjonale-eiere/ | title=Global Solidarity in Action: New owners of Ny Tid | work=[[Ny Tid]] | date=May 10, 2010 | accessdate=June 3, 2016| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100906132511/http://www.nytid.no/nyheter/artikler/20100510/ny-tid-far-internasjonale-eiere/ | archivedate=September 6, 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nHalvorssen's opinions have appeared in ''[[The New York Times]]'', ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', ''[[The Washington Post]]'', [[National Public Radio]], [[Time (magazine)|''Time'' magazine]], ''[[The Nation]]'' and ''[[National Journal]]'', and he has appeared on television outlets such as [[al-Jazeera]], [[BBC News]],<ref>{{cite press release |author=The Human Rights Foundation |url=http://humanrightsfoundation.org/news/hrf-on-bbc-world-news-tv-today-to-discuss-north-korea-balloon-launch-00349 |title=HRF on BBC World News TV Today to Discuss North Korea Balloon Launch &#124; News |publisher=The Human Rights Foundation |date=2014-01-22 |accessdate=2014-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505081553/http://humanrightsfoundation.org/news/hrf-on-bbc-world-news-tv-today-to-discuss-north-korea-balloon-launch-00349 |archive-date=2014-05-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> [[Fox News Channel]]\u2019s ''[[The O'Reilly Factor]]'' and ''[[Hannity & Colmes]]'', [[MSNBC]]\u2019s ''[[Hardball with Chris Matthews]]'', [[CNN]], and [[HBO]]. Thor Halvorssen was a speaker at [[TED (conference)|TEDx]] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]] in October 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thedp.com/article/tedxpenn-exceeded-expectations |title=TEDxPenn exceeded expectations |publisher=Thedp.com |date=2010-10-04 |accessdate=2014-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110518135620/http://thedp.com/article/tedxpenn-exceeded-expectations |archive-date=2011-05-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nHalvorssen testified to the U.S. Congress that he was the target of a smear campaign by [[Fusion GPS]]. Halvorssen provided testimony to the U.S. Senate Judiciary Committee in July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Halvorssen|first1=Thor|title=Here is my testimony to U.S. @senjudiciary committee about paid smear campaigns of #FusionGPS #Derwick #Venezuela \u2026|url=https://twitter.com/ThorHalvorssen/status/889989736718254080|website=twitter.com|accessdate=29 July 2017|date=25 July 2017|quote=https://www.scribd.com/document/354721041/Testimony-of-Thor-Halvorssen-to-the-Senate-Committee-on-the-Judiciary-7-26-2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Lee|title='Fusion GPS' Sleazy Venezuela Links Shed New Light on Trump Dossier|url=http://www.tabletmag.com/jewish-news-and-politics/241812/news-for-hire-scandal-deepens-gps-fusion-sleazy-venezuela-links-shed-new-light-on-trump-dossier|website=tabletmag.com|publisher=Tablet Magazine|accessdate=29 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nHalvorssen was born in Venezuela to Hilda Mendoza, a descendant and a relative, respectively, of Venezuela's first president [[Crist\u00f3bal Mendoza]] and liberator [[Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar]]. His father is [[Thor Halvorssen Hellum]], who served as a Venezuelan Ambassador for anti-Narcotic Affairs in the administration of [[Carlos Andr\u00e9s P\u00e9rez]] and as special overseas investigator of a Venezuelan Senate Commission. His family was prosperous and on his father's side he is the grandson of \u00d8ystein Halvorssen, who served as Norway's [[Consul (representative)|honorary consul-general]] in [[Caracas]]<ref>''[[Aftenposten]]'', 26 August 1947, p. 5</ref> and who \"built a family dynasty as the Venezuelan representative for corporations including [[Dunlop Rubber|Dunlop]], [[Alfa Laval]] and [[Ericsson]].\"<ref name=NYT07>[[Strausbaugh, John]] (August 19, 2007). [https://www.nytimes.com/2007/08/19/movies/19stra.html \"A Maverick Mogul, Proudly Politically Incorrect\"].  ''[[New York Times]]''. (Archived by [[WebCite]] [https://web.archive.org/web/20110511214626/http://www.nytimes.com:80/2007/08/19/movies/19stra.html? here.])</ref> His cousin is [[Leopoldo Lopez]].<ref>Halvorssen, Thor (March 14, 2012). [http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/opinion/perspectives/hugo-chavez-channels-the-dead-259423/?print=1 \"Hugo Chavez channels the dead\".] ''Pittsburgh Post Gazette''</ref> a Venezuelan politician, activist, and a political prisoner after called for peaceful protests in February 2014.\n\nHalvorssen attended the [[University of Pennsylvania]] and graduated [[Phi Beta Kappa]] and [[magna cum laude]], with concurrent undergraduate and graduate degrees in Political Science and History.\n\n===Father's imprisonment===\nHalvorssen\u2019s father, also named [[Thor Halvorssen (businessman)|Thor Halvorssen,]] was a wealthy businessman who was named the CEO of Venezuela's state TV CANTV<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cantv.com.ve/Portales/Cantv/Data/CANTVINF06/06_presidentes.asp|title=Can TV Past Presidents|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>. In 1989, then-President Carlos Andres Perez appointed Halvorssen Sr. as Venezuela\u2019s \u201canti-drug ambassador.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qaS0CwAAQBAJ&lpg=PA139&ots=CWu0sIyA-N&dq=Those%20Halvorssen%20anti%20drug%20tzar&pg=PA139#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Drug Politics: Dirty Money and Democracies|last=Jordan|first=David C.|date=2016-01-22|publisher=University of Oklahoma Press|year=|isbn=978-0-8061-7221-7|location=|pages=139|language=en}}</ref>\u201d \n\nWhen Halvorssen was a freshman at the University of Pennsylvania,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Grady |first1=Rosie |title=Is This The Face Of A New Global Human Rights Movement? |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/rosiegray/is-this-the-face-of-a-new-global-human-rights-movement |publisher=Buzzfeed News |accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref> in 1993, his father was arrested while investigating the [[Medell\u00edn cartel]] for [[money laundering]] and [[bank fraud]]. His father was tortured, beaten, and in danger of being murdered<ref name=\"foes\" /> during his 74-day incarceration in a Caracas jail on \"trumped-up\" charges of terrorism.<ref name=\"Hilton\">[[Isabel Hilton|Hilton, Isabel]]. \"Presumed Guilty\".  ''[[Gentlemen's Quarterly]] (GQ)'' UK: July 1994.</ref><ref name=\"Fonzi\">Fonzi, Gaeton. \"The Troublemaker\". ''[[The Pennsylvania Gazette]]'' (November 1994)</ref><ref name=\"talcual20010829\">{{cite web|url=http://www.talcualdigital.com/ediciones/2001/08/29/p9s1.htm|title=Recuerdos del terrorismo caraque\u00f1o|accessdate=March 3, 2007|publisher=[[Tal Cual]]|date=August 29, 2001|first=Manuel|last=Malaver |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20040823191004/http://www.talcualdigital.com/ediciones/2001/08/29/p9s1.htm |archivedate = August 23, 2004|language=es}}</ref> Halvorssen led the campaign for his father\u2019s release, garnering help from [[Amnesty International]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Grady |first1=Rosie |title=Is This The Face Of A New Global Human Rights Movement? |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/rosiegray/is-this-the-face-of-a-new-global-human-rights-movement |publisher=Buzzfeed News |accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref> which issued protests along with other International organizations. Halvorssen was eventually found not guilty of all charges. After his release the [[United Nations]]-affiliated [[International Society for Human Rights]] appointed him director of their Pan-American Committee.<ref name=\"foes\">[http://www.csmonitor.com/1993/1220/20012.html Venezuelan Anti-Drug Official Fights His Foes From a Prison Cell:] Evidence suggests Thor Halvorssen was framed by Colombian drug lords and their Caracas `friends'; ''[[Christian Science Monitor]]''. Boston, Mass.: Dec 20, 1993.</ref><ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/1993/1224/24102.html Former Venezuelan Drug Official Freed;] ''Christian Science Monitor''. Boston, Mass.: Dec 24, 1993.</ref><ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  The Americas: The price of vigilance in Venezuela's banking community. ''[[Wall Street Journal]]''. New York, N.Y.: Mar 4, 1994. pg. A9 [http://oilwars.blogspot.com/2005/06/good-old-days-iii.html Available online here.]</ref>\n\n===Mother's shooting===\nWhile attending a peaceful protest of the [[Venezuelan recall referendum of 2004]], Halvorssen's mother, Hilda Mendoza Denham, a British subject, was shot.<ref>[http://www.eursoc.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/593/Briton_Shot_In_Venezuela.html Briton Shot In Venezuela.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928202339/http://www.eursoc.com/news/fullstory.php/aid/593/Briton_Shot_In_Venezuela.html |date=2007-09-28 }} EURSOC, (August 19, 2004).  Retrieved on September 14, 2006.</ref>  Images of government supporters firing upon the demonstrators were captured by a live television broadcast.<ref name=OtraVez>{{in lang|es}} Olivares, Francisco. [http://archivo.eluniversal.com/2004/09/05/pol_art_05154A.shtml Otra vez los pistoleros.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710184947/http://archivo.eluniversal.com/2004/09/05/pol_art_05154A.shtml |date=2011-07-10 }} ''[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]]'' (5 September 2004).  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref><ref>{{in lang|es}} [http://urru.org/fotos/0_2004/20040816_NuevaMasacreAltamira.htm Fotos de la nueva masacre de Altamira, 2004.08.16] urru.org. Retrieved on September 14, 2006.</ref>  ''[[Wall Street Journal|The Wall Street Journal]]'' published an article written by Halvorssen about the shooting of his mother by members of the Venezuelan government security apparatus.<ref>Halvorssen, Thor L. The Price of Dissent in Venezuela.  ''Wall Street Journal'' (Eastern edition), Aug 19, 2004. p. A.12 Discussed online [https://web.archive.org/web/20041212014551/http://www.newsmax.com/archives/articles/2004/8/20/131240.shtml here.]</ref> The gunmen were later apprehended, tried, had their sentences revoked, tried again, found guilty, and received 3-year sentences for murder and for bodily harm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://merida.tsj.gov.ve/decisiones/2007/agosto/1812-22-359-06-.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-08-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110821193753/http://merida.tsj.gov.ve/decisiones/2007/agosto/1812-22-359-06-.html |archivedate=2011-08-21 }}</ref><ref>[http://mensual.prensa.com/mensual/contenido/2006/04/11/hoy/mundo/563578.html Revocan condena a \u2018pistoleros de Altamira\u2019.] ''Prensa.com'' (11 April 2006)</ref> They were released after serving six months in prison.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Arenas|first1=Macky|title=El ABC de Katty Ron / Hermana de Maritza Ron, asesinada en Plaza Altamira \"Mi hermana vino a votar para el Revocatorio, sin imaginar que encontrar\u00eda la muerte\"|url=http://www.abcdelasemana.com/2014/07/24/el-abc-de-katty-ron-hermana-de-maritza-ron-asesinada-en-plaza-altamirami-hermana-vino-a-votar-para-el-revocatorio-sin-imaginar-que-encontraria-la-muerte/|website=abcdelasemana.com|publisher=ABC de la Semana|date=2014}}</ref>\n\n==Activism==\nHalvorssen has a specialty on matters regarding dictatorships, [[human trafficking]], slavery, and threats to democracy. He has lectured widely on the subject of human rights including at [[Harvard Law School]], the New York City Junto, the [[United Nations Association]] in New York, and the [[American Enterprise Institute]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hclaweb.org/conference/panels-speakers/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-06-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100621040821/http://hclaweb.org/conference/panels-speakers/ |archivedate=2010-06-21 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nycjunto.com/library/2007/05/Halvorssen.htm |title=The New York City Junto |website=Nycjunto.com |date=2007-05-03 |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unanyc.org/events/archive/2008/20080320_halvorssen.html |title=UNA-NY: Event Archive |website=Unanyc.org |date=2008-03-20 |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aei.org/event/1439 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-06-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100531083028/http://www.aei.org/event/1439 |archivedate=2010-05-31 }}</ref> Halvorssen has also spoken at the British parliament.<ref name=TRTP>{{cite web|title=The Responsibility to Protect|url=http://henryjacksonsociety.org/2011/11/08/the-responsibility-to-protect/|publisher=The Henry Jackson Society|accessdate=3 May 2012}}</ref>. Alongside Harvard Law School dean [[Martha Minow]] he testified to the U.S. Commission on Unalienable Rights of the U.S. State Department.[https://www.state.gov/commission-on-unalienable-rights]\n\n===Lucent Technologies===\nIn 1999, Halvorssen spearheaded a campaign on the floor of the [[Lucent|Lucent Technologies]] annual shareholder meeting appealing for the creation of an anti-slave labor policy whereby Lucent would require China to certify that Lucent's products were not fabricated using [[slave labor]].  China's [[Laogai]] camps allegedly imprison eight million men, women, and children in 1100 factories, farms, and other facilities producing a wide range of consumer products.<ref>[http://www.newstrolls.com/news/dev/guest/022299.htm Lucent Stockowners Want Anti-Slave Labor Policy for China Operations.] Retrieved on August 26, 2006. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051215010656/http://www.newstrolls.com/news/dev/guest/022299.htm |date=December 15, 2005 }}</ref>\n\n===Foundation for Individual Rights in Education===\nIn 1999, Halvorssen became the first executive director and chief executive officer of the [[Foundation for Individual Rights in Education]] (FIRE), a U.S. civil liberties organization. As head of FIRE, Halvorssen formed coalitions that brought together the conservative and libertarian advocacy organizations such as the [[Heritage Foundation]], Feminists for Free Expression, the [[Eagle Forum]], with more traditional free speech defenders such as the [[ACLU]].  Halvorssen has a track record of defending individuals both on the right<ref>[[William F. Buckley|Buckley, William F. Jr.]]  [http://www.nationalreview.com/buckley/buckleyprint041001.html Who Do We Blame?  The case of a YAF student chapter at Penn State.] ''[[National Review]]'' (April 10, 2001).  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> and on the left of the political spectrum.<ref>Carlson, Scott.  [http://chronicle.com/free/2002/09/2002092703t.htm University Orders Student Group to Remove Online Link to a Rebel Group's Web Site.]  ''[[The Chronicle of Higher Education]]'' (September 27, 2002). Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref>\n\nIn 2001, Halvorssen stated that, \"Liberty of opinion, speech, and expression is indispensable to a free and, in the deepest sense, progressive society. Deny it to one, and you deny it effectively to all. These truths long have been ignored and betrayed on our campuses, to the peril of a free society.\"<ref>Halvorssen, Thor L. [http://www.boundless.org/2001/departments/campus_culture/a0000505.html Campus Tyranny.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050318051352/http://www.boundless.org/2001/departments/campus_culture/a0000505.html |date=2005-03-18 }} Retrieved on August 26, 2006.</ref>  In a 2003 moderated chat, he said, \"History has taught us that a society that does not respect individual rights, freedom of conscience, and freedom of speech will not long survive as a free society in any form.\"<ref>[http://chronicle.com/colloquylive/2003/04/speech/ Tests for Academic Freedom in a Time of War.]  ''The Chronicle of Higher Education''. (April 17, 2003). Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref>\n\n===Human Rights Foundation===\nHalvorssen stepped down as head of FIRE in March 2004 to join its Board of Advisors and announced the creation of an international group that would \"champion the definition of human rights that originally animated the human rights movement, centered on the twin concepts of freedom of self-determination and freedom from tyranny.\"<ref name=dartreview>Glabe, Scott L. [http://dartreview.com/archives/2005/11/22/new_organization_opens_fire_on_chavez.php New Organization Opens Fire on Chavez] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081120103351/http://dartreview.com/archives/2005/11/22/new_organization_opens_fire_on_chavez.php |date=November 20, 2008 }}, ''[[The Dartmouth Review]]'', November 22, 2005. Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> HRF was incorporated in 2005, opening its headquarters in [[New York City]] in August 2006. Its International Council includes several well-known prisoners of conscience such as [[Elie Wiesel]], [[Harry Wu]], and [[Vladimir Bukovsky]]. It also includes democracy activists such as [[Mart Laar]], and [[Garry Kasparov]]. Its chairman until his death in December 2011, was [[V\u00e1clav Havel]].\n\nAt the helm of HRF Halvorssen has repeatedly lobbied and advocated for the release of Chinese political prisoner [[Liu Xiaobo]].<ref name=\"HR Big Winner\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=Human Rights Is Big Winner in Nobel Peace Prize Selection|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/human-rights-is-big-winne_b_756042.html|accessdate=3 May 2012|newspaper=The Huffington Post|date=October 8, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Truth Outweigh\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=Truth will Outweigh the Chinese Dictatorship--Liu Xiaobo's Freedom is the Test|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/truth-will-outweigh-the-c_b_800537.html|accessdate=3 May 2012|newspaper=The Huffington Post|date=December 23, 2010}}</ref>  In 2010 Halvorssen was special guest of Liu Xiaobo at the Nobel Prize ceremony awarding the prize to Liu Xiaobo in absentia.<ref name=\"HRF Support\">{{cite web|title=HRF announces its membership in the International Committee to Support Liu Xiaobo|url=http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/media/HRFannouncesitsmembershipintheInternationalCommitteetoSupportLiuXiaobo12092011.html|publisher=Human Rights Foundation|accessdate=3 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310181103/http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/media/HRFannouncesitsmembershipintheInternationalCommitteetoSupportLiuXiaobo12092011.html|archive-date=10 March 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"NPP Winners\">{{cite news|title=Nobel Peace Prize winners campaign to release Chinese dissident Liu Xiaobo|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/8945006/Nobel-Peace-Prize-winners-campaign-to-release-Chinese-dissident-Liu-Xiaobo.html|publisher=The Telegraph|accessdate=3 May 2012|location=London|date=December 9, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"Winners Urge\">{{cite news|title=Nobel winners urge China to release Liu Xiaobo|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/feedarticle/9987302|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=3 May 2012|location=London|date=January 23, 2008}}</ref> Halvorssen is identified as a supporter of Chinese [[Uyghur people|Uyghur]] leader [[Rebiya Kadeer]] and has sharply criticized the Tawainese [[Kuomintang]] government for its banning visits by Kadeer.<ref name=\"Fails to Learn\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=Taiwan Fails to Learn From Its Own History|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/taiwan-fails-to-learn-fro_1_b_684936.html|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=3 May 2012|date=August 17, 2010}}</ref> Halvorssen has supported UN-level action to address the violations of Uyghur rights in China.\n\nHalvorssen appears as a frequent critic of [[Uganda]]\u2019s president [[Yoweri Museveni]] and, in particular, the legislative efforts in Uganda to punish [[homosexuality]] with the death penalty.<ref name=\"UN Okay\">{{cite news|last=Halvorssen|first=Thor|title=United Nations: It's Okay to Kill the Gay|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/united-nations-its-okay-t_b_787024.html|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=3 May 2012|date=November 23, 2010}}</ref>\nHalvorssen is a critic of [[Hugo Ch\u00e1vez]],<ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/005/177yckaw.asp Guerrilla Nation.]  ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' (January 26, 2005).</ref> and has written on Venezuela\u2019s [[anti-Semitism]] and the assault on democracy and individual rights in [[Latin America]].<ref name=Hurricane>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/005/903jhsjt.asp?pg=1 Hurricane Hugo.]  ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'', August 8, 2005, Volume 010, Issue 44.  Also available at [http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0RMQ/is_44_10/ai_n14895831/print LookSmart.]</ref> Halvorssen's criticisms have also been directed at U.S. Republicans such as [[Jack Kemp]]<ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/002/785ruylo.asp?pg=2 Hugo Chavez vs. the Media.] ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' (June 9, 2003).</ref> as well as Democrats including [[John Conyers]] and [[Jos\u00e9 Enrique Serrano|Jose Serrano]].<ref>Halvorssen, Thor.  [http://www.weeklystandard.com/Content/Public/Articles/000/000/002/346jorji.asp Comandante Chavez's Friends.]  ''[[The Weekly Standard]]'' (March 11, 2003).</ref> In a symposium published by the American conservative magazine ''[[National Review]]'', he condemned [[Augusto Pinochet]] for his human rights abuses.<ref>Halvorssen, Thor (December 11, 2006). [https://archive.is/20120527052919/http://article.nationalreview.com/300658/pinochet-is-history/nro-symposium Pinochet Is History.] National Review Online Symposium.  Retrieved on February 21, 2010.</ref><ref>Knapp, Alex (December 13, 2006). [http://www.outsidethebeltway.com/archives/another_symposium_of_denial/ Another Symposium of Denial.] Outside the Beltway. Retrieved on February 21, 2010.</ref> Halvorssen led a campaign to expose [[Chechnya|Chechen]] president [[Ramzan Kadyrov]]\u2019s human rights violations and ultimately created a firestorm for Hollywood actress [[Hilary Swank]] after she accepted a cash payment to celebrate Kadyrov\u2019s birthday.<ref name=\"Party Criticism\">{{cite news|title=Hilary Swank under fire for attending Ramzan Kadyrov's party in Chechnya|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/oct/11/hilary-swank-ramzan-kadyrov-chechnya|accessdate=3 May 2012|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|first=Ben|last=Child|date=October 11, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"PR Disaster\">{{cite news|title=Hilary Swank sacks manager and staff following Ramzan Kadyrov PR disaster|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/oct/31/hilary-swank-sacks-manager|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=3 May 2012|location=London|first=Ben|last=Child|date=October 31, 2011}}</ref>  In the same manner Halvorssen has exposed payments from dictators to [[Jennifer Lopez]], [[Erykah Baduh]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[Nelly Furtado]], and [[50 Cent]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Daunt|first1=Tina|title=Jennifer Lopez Accused of Accepting $10 Million From 'Dictators and Crooks'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennifer-lopez-accused-accepting-10-584679 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Human Rights Group Slams Mariah Carey for Concert in Angola|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/human-rights-group-slams-mariah-666951|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Halvorssen|first1=Thor|last2=Gladstein|first2=Alex|title=Erykah Badu\u2019s Oppressively Apolitical Stance on Human Rights|url=http://time.com/85126/erykah-badu-swaziland-human-rights/|website=time.com|publisher=Time|date=2014}}</ref>\n\nOther advocacy campaigns include [[Panama]]\u2019s president [[Ricardo Martinelli]] on freedom of speech violations; political prisoner cases in [[Venezuela]], [[Vietnam]], [[Cuba]], and [[Bolivia]]; as well as the rights of human rights defenders in [[Colombia]].\n\n===Oslo Freedom Forum===\n{{main|Oslo Freedom Forum}}\nIn 2009, Halvorssen founded a global gathering of human rights advocates called the Oslo Freedom Forum. It has taken place in Oslo annually since then.  According to ''[[Wired Magazine]]'', \"if the global human-rights movement were to create its own unified representative body, it would look something like this.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rowan|first1=David|title=Oslo Freedom Forum brings together the global human rights movement|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2012-05/14/30-things-i-learned-at-the-oslo-freedom-forum|website=[[Wired Magazine]]|publisher=Conde Nast UK|date=2014|access-date=2017-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160419092201/http://www.wired.co.uk/news/archive/2012-05/14/30-things-i-learned-at-the-oslo-freedom-forum|archive-date=2016-04-19|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nNorwegian newspaper ''[[Verdens Gang]]'' called it a \"Gathering of Heroes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hanneskartveit.vgb.no/2010/05/28/heltene-samles-i-oslo/ |title=Heltene samles i Oslo |publisher=Hanne Skartveit |date=2010-05-28 |accessdate=2014-05-24 |language=no |trans-title=The heroes gather in Oslo}}</ref>  ''[[The Economist]]'' calls it the \"Davos of Human Rights.\" Participants include [[Pussy Riot]]'s [[Nadezhda Tolokonnikova]] and [[Maria Aliokhina]], Sudan's [[Lubna al-Hussein]], Burma's [[Aung San Suu Kyi]], China's [[Ai Weiwei]], Tahrir Square protest organizer [[Wael Ghonim]], Wikipedia founder [[Jimmy Wales]], Holocaust survivor [[Elie Wiesel]], Iran's [[Marina Nemat]], [[Peter Thiel]], [[Julian Assange]], [[V\u00e1clav Havel]], [[Garry Kasparov]], [[Leopoldo Lopez]], Nobel laureate [[Lech Walesa]], and Russian political prisoner [[Mikhail Khodorkovskii]].\n\n===Children's Peace Movement===\nSince 2009, Halvorssen is listed as \"Patron\" of the Children's Peace Movement, On Own Feet.  Known as the \"Centipede Movement\" it is a Czech-based group that facilitates bilateral relations between children and adolescents in [[Poland]], the [[Czech Republic]], [[Slovakia]], [[Canada]], and [[Norway]] with children in war-torn countries such as [[Afghanistan]] and [[Iraq]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/thor-halvorssen/a-different-kind-of-army_b_574450.html |title=A Different Kind of Army |publisher=[[The Huffington Post]] |date= |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.stonozka.org/ |title=Hnut\u00ed Na vlastn\u00edch nohou - Stono\u017eka |website=Stonozka.org |date= |accessdate=2017-03-13}}</ref> The previous Patron was former Czech president [[V\u00e1clav Havel]].\n\n==Film==\nHalvorssen executive produced ''Hammer & Tickle'', a film about the power of humor, ridicule, and satire as the language of truth under Soviet tyranny. This film premiered at Tribeca in 2006.<ref name=\"IMDb\" /> The film won Best New Documentary Film at the [[Zurich Film Festival]].<ref>[http://www.zurichfilmfestival.org/en/welcome/detail/article/81/4/ Closing Night of the 2nd Zurich Film Festival.]{{dead link|date=January 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}} [[Zurich Film Festival]] (October 10, 2006).  Retrieved on December 9, 2006.</ref>\n\nHalvorssen co-produced the film ''Freedom's Fury'' which was executive produced by [[Lucy Liu]], [[Quentin Tarantino]], and [[Andrew Vajna]]. It premiered at the [[Tribeca Film Festival]].<ref name=\"IMDb\">{{IMDb name|id=1812816}} Retrieved on August 26, 2006.</ref><ref>Cold War Tale Told at Last. ''[[New York Post]]'' (April 29, 2006). [http://pqarchiver.nypost.com/nypost/access/1029793191.html?dids=1029793191:1029793191&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Apr+29%2C+2006&author=&pub=New+York+Post&edition=&startpage=011&desc=COLD+WAR+TALE+TOLD+AT+LAST Available online.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714220157/http://pqarchiver.nypost.com/nypost/access/1029793191.html?dids=1029793191:1029793191&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Apr+29,+2006&author=&pub=New+York+Post&edition=&startpage=011&desc=COLD+WAR+TALE+TOLD+AT+LAST |date=2011-07-14 }}</ref> The film relates the story of the [[Hungarian Revolution of 1956|uprising against the government that occurred in Hungary]] in 1956.\n\nHalvorssen is producer of the film ''The Singing Revolution'', a film about [[Estonia]]'s peaceful struggle for political independence from [[Occupation of the Baltic states|Soviet occupation]].<ref name=SR>[http://www.singingrevolution.com/cgi-local/content.cgi?pg=1&p=3 The Singing Revolution.] Official website.  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> The film premiered at the [[Black Nights Film Festival]] in December 2006 where it received a 15-minute standing ovation.<ref>[http://www.singingrevolution.com/cgi-local/reviews.cgi Reviews.] The Singing Revolution.  Retrieved on September 9, 2008.</ref> Since then, it has become the most successful documentary film in Estonian box-office history.<ref>[http://www.estosite.org/home/?page_id=23 Singing Revolution.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100212123502/http://www.estosite.org/home/?page_id=23 |date=2010-02-12 }} Estosite.org.  Retrieved on February 21, 2010.</ref>\n\nHalvorssen produced ''The Dissident'' in 2019, a film about the murder of Saudi journalist [[Jamal Khashoggi]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Glieberman |first1=Owen |title=\u2018The Dissident\u2019: Film Review |url=\u2018The Dissident\u2019: Film Review |publisher=Variety |accessdate=21 February 2020}}</ref> The film was directed by Academy-Award winning director [[Bryan Fogel]]. [https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/dissident-review-1272803]\n\n===Filmography===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Thor Halvorssen's Filmography<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1812816/|title=Thor Halvorssen|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n!Title \n!Year \n!Role \n|-\n|Hammer & Tickle \n|2006\n|Producer\n|-\n|Freedom's Fury \n|2006\n|Producer\n|-\n|The Singing Revolution\n|2006\n|Producer\n|-\n|The Sugar Babies\n|2007\n|Producer\n|-\n|Indoctrinate U \n|2007\n|Producer\n|-\n|2081 \n|2009\n|Producer\n|-\n|Pups of Liberty\n|2009\n|Executive Producer\n|-\n|U.N. Me \n|2009\n|Executive Producer\n|-\n|State of Control\n|2016\n|Producer\n|-\n|The Dissident \n|2020\n|Producer\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nUniversity of Pennsylvania president [[Judith Rodin]] honored Halvorssen's achievements by awarding him the Sol Feinstone Award for protecting student speech.<ref>[http://www.publiceye.org/ifas/cnp/bios/halth.html Thor Halvorssen.]  PublicEye.org Retrieved 26 August 2006.</ref>\n\nIn 2010 Romanian leader [[Emil Constantinescu]] presented Halvorssen with a presidential silver medal to commemorate the tenth anniversary of the [[Romanian Revolution of 1989]]. \"On behalf of those who fought and died for freedom, I present this medal to the Oslo Freedom Forum founder, and remind those here that even if Romanians live in democracy now, we cannot feel entirely free as long as other people \u2013 who live under dictatorial and repressive regimes anywhere in the world \u2013 are not also be free.\"<ref>[http://thehrf.org/media/042910.html ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110728094549/http://thehrf.org/media/042910.html |date=July 28, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Halvorssen was awarded the Millennium Candler Justice Prize, honoring leadership in effecting positive social change, presented at the [[Millennium Gate Museum]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://thegatemuseum.org/gala-2018-millennium-candler-honorees/|title=Millennium Gate Museum {{!}}   2018 Millennium Candler Honorees|website=thegatemuseum.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-26}}</ref> The prize was previously awarded to Former First Lady Rosalynn Carter and to Prince Jean of Orl\u00e9ans, Dauphin of France.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mdjonline.com/neighbor_newspapers/northside_sandy_springs/community/national-monuments-foundation-sends-delegation-to-denmark-announces-awards/article_e8a2fde0-a228-11e7-a7e9-f30ea43f0159.html|title=National Monuments Foundation sends delegation to Denmark, announces 2018 awards|last=Staff|first=Neighbor|work=MDJOnline.com|access-date=2018-10-26|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\n* Halvorssen, Thor L (1996). [https://books.google.com/books?id=HLSjNwAACAAJ&dq=thor+halvorssen ''Sim\u00f3n Bol\u00edvar and the Enlightenment''], University of Pennsylvania.\n\n== Notes ==\n:{{note label|FullName|a|a}} Halvorssen Mendoza is known commonly as Thor Halvorssen.  Per Venezuelan naming conventions, his full legal name includes both his father's (Halvorssen) and mother's (Mendoza) surnames. His full, legal, Venezuelan name distinguishes him from his father, [[Thor Halvorssen Hellum]]. (See [https://web.archive.org/web/20070706171607/http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/es/thor-es.html Thor Halvorssen - Presidente.] The Human Rights Foundation.  Retrieved on July 21, 2007. {{in lang|es}} Also see [https://archive.is/20130415000554/http://www.humanrightsfoundation.org/reports/hcletter.html re: Francisco Us\u00f3n\u2014Political Prisoner and Prisoner of Conscience.]  Human Rights Foundation.  Retrieved on July 21, 2007.)\n\n==References==