{"title_page": "Bhad Bhabie", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{pp-pc1|expiry=June 1, 2020}}\n{{short description|American rapper and media personality}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Bhad Bhabie\n| image            = \n| image_upright    = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = Danielle Peskowitz Bregoli\n| alias            = \n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|2003|03|26}}\n| birth_place      = [[Boynton Beach, Florida]], U.S.\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date first) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[Trap music (hip hop)|trap]]}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Rapper|Media personality}}\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n* B.H.A.D. Music\n}}\n| associated_acts  = <!-- per infobox musical artist template list only associations that are longer than a song or two\n-->\n| website          = {{URL|http://www.bhadbhabie.com}}\n| module           = \n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n}}\n\n'''Danielle Peskowitz Bregoli'''<ref name=\"Wapo2017-02-12\" /> (born March 26, 2003),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8261436/bhad-bhabie-lil-yachty-gucci-flip-flops|title=Bhad Bhabie Celebrates 15th Birthday With New Song 'Gucci Flip Flops,' Feat. Lil Yachty|author=|date=|website=Billboard|accessdate=March 6, 2019}}</ref> also known by her [[stage name]] '''Bhad Bhabie''' ({{IPAc-en|b|\u00e6|d|_|'|b|e\u026a|b|i\u02d0}}, \"bad baby\"), is an American rapper and [[internet personality]] from Boynton Beach, Florida. She first became known from an episode of ''[[Dr. Phil (talk show)|Dr. Phil]]'' in September 2016, in which she said the phrase, \"Catch me outside, how about that?\", which became a [[viral video]] [[meme (Internet)|meme]] and [[catchphrase]].<ref name=Wapo2017-02-12/><ref name=\"NYP\">{{cite news|last1=Musumeci|first1=Natalie|title='Cash me outside' girl sentenced to 5 years probation|url=https://nypost.com/2017/08/02/cash-me-outside-girl-sentenced-to-5-years-probation/|publisher=The New York Post|date=August 2, 2017}}</ref> In 2017, Bregoli became the youngest female rapper ever to appear on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart with her debut single \"[[These Heaux]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100/2017-09-23|title=Top 100 songs|website=Billboard.com|date=|accessdate=September 15, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/cash-me-outside-girl-signs-atlantic-records-contract-1202561216/|title='Cash Me Outside' Girl Signs With Atlantic Records: 'A Real Star With Undeniable Talent,' Says Label Executive|last=Staff|first=Variety|date=September 16, 2017|work=Variety|accessdate=February 26, 2018}}</ref> She subsequently signed a record deal with [[Atlantic Records]] and has now expanded into a reality show, a makeup brand, tours, and a music career. Bregoli released her first mixtape, ''[[15 (mixtape)|15]]'', in September 2018.\nIts lead single, \"[[Hi Bich]]\", became her second single to appear on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 chart.\n\n== Early life ==\nBregoli was born in [[Boynton Beach, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/rta902/from-boynton-to-bel-air-ft-danielle-bregoli-cash-me-outside-girl-create-62522c181cb|title=From Boynton to Bel Air ft Danielle Bregoli: 'Cash Me Outside' girl #Create|last=Davidson|first=Sora|date=February 14, 2018|website=medium.com|accessdate=March 6, 2019}}</ref> Her parents, Ira Peskowitz and Barbara Ann Bregoli, dated for a year before Bregoli's mother became pregnant, later separating when she was an infant. She grew up in Boynton Beach, a city in Palm Beach County, in South Florida. Her father is [[Jewish]] and her mother is of [[Italians|Italian]] descent.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/03/magazine/the-big-business-of-becoming-bhad-bhabie.html|title=The Big Business of Becoming Bhad Bhabie|last=Keiles|first=Jamie Lauren|date=July 3, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=December 4, 2018|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref> Bregoli was raised in a [[Catholic]]{{citation needed|date=June 2019}} household primarily by her mother, and is estranged from her father, a deputy who works for the [[Palm Beach, Florida|Palm Beach]] [[Palm Beach County Sheriff's Office|County Sheriff's Office]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/state/florida/article143044869.html|title=A church using 'Cash Me Outside' to draw in members? How bow dah?|last=Neal|first=David J|date=April 6, 2017|work=Miami Herald|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mypalmbeachpost.com/news/breaking-news/exclusive-dad-wants-cash-outside-girl-out-hollywood-therapy/tUXIH2VLp77qrmqtmXW1KI/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Dad wants Cash Me Outside girl out of Hollywood, in therapy|last=Duret|first=Daphne|date=March 22, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017|publisher=My Palm Beach Post}}</ref>\n\nShe has stated that she dates boys and girls in her song \"[[15 (mixtape)|Bhad Bhabie Outro]]\" and that she lived with her former girlfriend, Gabby. However, she has not put a label or confirmed her sexuality.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/bhad-bhabie-girlfriend-mixtape/|title=Bhad Bhabie raps about former girlfriend on debut mixtape|date=September 19, 2018|website=The Daily Dot}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\n===2016\u20132017: ''Dr. Phil'' appearance, rehab, and legal issues===\nOn September 14, 2016, Bregoli and her mother, Barbara Ann, were interviewed on ''[[Dr. Phil (talk show)|Dr. Phil]]'' for the segment \"I Want To Give Up My Car-Stealing, Knife-Wielding, Twerking 13-Year-Old Daughter Who Tried To Frame Me For A Crime\" to discuss Bregoli's behavior, which included stealing a crew member's car while the episode was being filmed. When Bregoli became irritated at the laughter that the audience exhibited at her expense, she responded to them by saying \"Catch me outside, how about that?\", jokingly challenging them to a fight outside the studio; her accent made the phrase sound like \"Cash me ousside, how bout dah\u201d which became a meme and Bregoli became known as the \"'Cash Me Outside' Girl\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=stubblebine|first1=allison|title=A Timeline of Danielle Bregoli's (a.k.a. the 'Cash Me Outside' Girl) Rise to Celebrity|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/7968844/danielle-bregolis-cash-me-outside-girl-timeline|accessdate=February 11, 2018|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=September 19, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Desantis|first=Rachel|title=Cash me ousside teen to Dr. Phil \u2013 You were nothing before me|url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/02/10/cash-me-ousside-danielle-bregoli-dr-phil/|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=February 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>Zimmerman, Amy (February 10, 2017). [http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/02/10/cash-me-outside-girl-danielle-bregoli-tries-to-cash-in-on-fame.html \"'Cash Me Outside' Girl Danielle Bregoli Is Dr. Phil's Latest Victim\"]. [[The Daily Beast]].</ref><ref>Wilson, Samantha (February 7, 2017). [http://hollywoodlife.com/2017/02/07/who-is-danielle-peskowitz-bregoli-cash-me-outside-howbow-dah/ \"Danielle Peskowitz Bregoli: Who's The 'Cash Me Outside' Girl Everyone's Obsessed With?\"]. [[Hollywood Life]].</ref> On February 10, 2017, Bregoli reappeared on the show, but without the studio audience, due to the response at her previous appearance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv/cash-girl-returns-dr-phil-months-rehab-article-1.2969310|title='Cash me outside' girl returns to 'Dr. Phil' after months of treatment, slightly humbled|website=[[New York Daily News]]|first=Jessa|last=Schroder|date=February 10, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2017}}</ref> Her first appearance on the show, and the catchphrase it spawned, would inspire a single based on the clip, which was recorded by DJ Suede The Remix God, which entered the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Billboard Hot 100|Hot 100]], [[Streaming Songs]], and [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] charts in its March 4, 2017 issue. The song in turn led to a series of dance videos that were uploaded onto [[YouTube]].<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7702012/cash-me-outside-remix-hot-100-dj-suede-remix-god \"'Cash Me Outside' Remix Hits Hot 100 Thanks to Viral Dr. Phil Clip\"] from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''. February 24, 2017.</ref>\n\nBregoli and her mother sued three companies for \"infringing her intellectual property rights\" by using her signature catchphrase without consent.  She also threatened to sue [[Walmart]] for using her catchphrase on T-shirts.{{cn|date=January 2020}} She was nominated for the [[2017 MTV Movie & TV Awards]] in the [[2017 MTV Movie & TV Awards#Winners and nominees|\"Trending\"]] category based on the catchphrase.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lakshmin|first=Deepa|title=The \"Cash Me Outside\" Meme Is An MTV Movie & TV Awards Nominee, How Bout Dat?|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3008390/mtv-movie-tv-awards-2017-trending-best-musical-moment/|publisher=MTV|date=May 2, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref>\n\nFollowing her appearance on ''Dr. Phil'', Bregoli spent time at a [[Utah]] ranch for \"troubled teens\". She was later arrested and pleaded guilty to charges of grand theft, marijuana possession, and filing a false police report, for which she was sentenced to five years' probation in July 2017,<ref>Burke, Minyvonne (June 28, 2017). [http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/cash-girl-pleads-guilty-multiple-charges-article-1.3285527 \"'Cash Me Outside' girl Danielle Bregoli pleads guilty to grand theft, possession of marijuana and other charges\"]. ''[[New York Daily News]]''.</ref> but it ended earlier, in March 2018, after she hired a new lawyer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xxlmag.com/video/2018/03/bhad-bhabie-off-5-year-probation/|title=Bhad Bhabie Off Five-Year Probation \u2013 XXL|website=XXL Mag|accessdate=March 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u20132018: music beginnings, and ''15'' ===\nIn early 2017, Bregoli was signed by music manager [[Adam Kluger]] and initially received industry backlash.\n\n{{quote|text=\"Everybody got weird\" he says. \"I wasn't even mad that they were bashing Danielle, because everyone was bashing Danielle at the time. I was like: 'You really don't believe that I know what I'm doing? Don't bet the horse, bet the jockey.\"\"<ref>{{cite news|work=New York Times|date=July 3, 2018|title=The Big Business of Becoming Bhad Bhabie: How a troubled Florida teenager went from the \"Dr. Phil\" show to signing a major-label record deal as a rapper|author=Jamie Lauren Keiles | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/03/magazine/the-big-business-of-becoming-bhad-bhabie.html}}</ref>}}\n\nBy March 2017, Bregoli's personal worth was estimated to be $200,000.<ref name=LifeAndStyle2017-03-16/>\n\nBregoli released her first single \"[[These Heaux]]\" (pronounced \"hoes\") on August 24, 2017. The recording reached number 77 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], making Bregoli the youngest female rap artist to debut on the music chart.<ref>{{cite web|title=The 'Cash Me Ousside' Girl Just Dropped the Video for Her New Single, So Watch It Here and We Won't Tell Anyone|url=https://www.maxim.com/entertainment/these-heaux-music-video-2017-8|publisher=Maxim|accessdate=September 11, 2017|date=August 31, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title='Cash Me Outside' Girl Danielle Bregoli Verbally Attacks Her Dad in New Diss Track|url=http://www.lifeandstylemag.com/posts/cash-me-outside-girl-danielle-bregoli-slams-dad-new-song-141248|publisher=Life & Style|accessdate=September 23, 2017|author=Real, Evan|date=September 7, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/cash_me_outside_danielle_bregoli_atlantic_records|title='Cash Me Outside' girl Danielle Bregoli somehow lands contract with Atlantic Records|work=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]|accessdate=September 23, 2017|date=September 15, 2017}}</ref> The success of \"These Heaux\" prompted [[Atlantic Records]] to sign Bregoli to a multi-album recording contract.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/hip-hop/7965832/bhad-bhabie-cash-me-outside-record-deal|title='Cash Me Outside' Girl Inks Record Deal With Atlantic Records|author=Penrose, Nerisha|work=Billboard|accessdate=September 15, 2017}}</ref> In September 2017, she remixed the [[Kodak Black]] song \"[[Roll in Peace]]\" and [[Tee Grizzley]] and [[Lil Yachty]] song \"[[From the D to the A]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Danielle Bregoli drops her remix of Kodak Black & XXXTentacion's \"Roll In Peace.\"|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/danielle-bregoli-aka-bhad-babie-remixes-kodak-black-and-xxxtentacions-roll-in-peace-new-song.1975609.html|publisher=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=September 23, 2017|author=Findley, Mitch|date=September 7, 2017}}</ref> On September 22, 2017, she released \"[[Hi Bich]]\" which reached number 68 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and a day after, \"Whachu Know\", as a single alongside the video, which received over 3 million views in 24 hours.<ref>{{cite web|author=Hudelson, Molly|date=September 21, 2017|accessdate=September 22, 2017|work=Substream Magazine|title=\"Whachu Know\" about Bhad Bhabie? She's back with two new videos.|url=https://substreammagazine.com/2017/09/hi-bich-whachu-know-bhad-bhabie/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title='Cash Me Outside' Girl Danielle Bregoli Tells the Judge 'Hi Bich' in Latest Musical Opus (Video)|url=http://www.thewrap.com/cash-me-outside-girl-danielle-bregoli-tells-the-judge-hi-bich-in-latest-musical-opus-video/|author=Kenneally, Tim|publisher=The Wrap|date=September 21, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017|work=The Wrap}}</ref> After a shorter break, on November 30, 2017 she released another single \"I Got It\",<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8054740/bhad-bhabie-i-got-it-video-cash-me-ousside|title=Bhad Bhabie Is Bhack With 'I Got It' Song & Video|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 8, 2018}}</ref> followed by \"Mama Don't Worry (Still Ain't Dirty)\" in December. In the latter, she's rapping about her past, and that her appearance in ''Dr. Phil'' should be forgotten.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8063668/bhad-bhabie-dont-worry-still-aint-dirty|title=Bhad Bhabie Talks Making Bank on 'Mama Don't Worry (Still Ain't Dirty)': Listen|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 8, 2018}}</ref> This theme is echoed in the video for \"Both of Em\", in which she buries her old self in a shallow grave.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8092609/bhad-bhabie-both-of-em-video|title=Bhad Bhabie Is Reborn in 'Both of Em' Video|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 8, 2018}}</ref> In \"Hi Bich (Remix)\" she collaborates for the first time with other artists, including [[YBN Nahmir]], [[Rich the Kid]] and [[Asian Da Brat|Asian Doll]] (in the video, for unknown reasons YBN Nahmir was replaced by [[MadeinTYO]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/hip-hop/8094480/bhad-bhabies-hi-bish-remix-asian-doll-rich-the-kid-ybn-nahmir|title=Bhad Bhabie's 'Hi Bich' Remix Features Asian Doll, Rich the Kid & YBN Nahmir: Listen|work=billboard.com|accessdate=March 8, 2018}}</ref><ref name=hb>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8097699/bhad-bhabie-hi-bich-remix-video-asian-doll-rich-the-kid-madeintyo|title=Bhad Bhabie Hooks Up With Asian Doll, Rich the Kid & MadeinTYO for 'Hi Bich' Remix VIdeo|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn March 26, 2018, she celebrated her birthday with a new song release, \"Gucci Flip Flops\", featuring Lil Yachty.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8261436/bhad-bhabie-lil-yachty-gucci-flip-flops|title=Bhad Bhabie Celebrates 15th Birthday With New Song 'Gucci Flip Flops,' Feat. Lil Yachty|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 29, 2018}}</ref> Two days later, she received a gold certification from the RIAA for her single \"Hi Bich\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bhad-babie-scores-her-1st-gold-record-with-hi-bich-news.46632.html|title=Bhad Bhabie Scores Her 1st Gold Record With 'Hi Bich'|website=HotNewHipHop|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> In mid-April, she released a freestyle called \"Who Run It\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bhad-bhabie-drops-off-her-who-run-it-freestyle-new-song.1978149.html|title=Bhad Bhabie Drops Off Her \"Who Run It\" Freestyle|work=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\nHer first tour across North America and Europe, together with Asian Doll, began on April 14, 2018, performing the first and second legs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8232172/bhad-bhabie-north-american-tour-dates|title=Bhad Bhabie to Headline North American Tour|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn May 2, 2018, the video for \"Gucci Flip Flops\" was released. Following the video's release, the song debuted on Billboard's Hot 100 Chart at number 80, becoming her third charting single on the chart. She received a 2018 Billboard Music Award nomination in the category of Best Female Rap Artist, along with Cardi B and Nicki Minaj.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8456339/bhad-bhabie-bbma-nomination-video-interview|title=Watch Bhad Bhabie Talk Billboard Music Awards Nomination, Nicki Minaj & Cardi B, Working With Ty Dolla $ign, More|website=Billboard|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn June 14, 2018, Bregoli released another single \"Trust Me\" featuring [[Ty Dolla Sign]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/06/bhad-bhabie-recruits-ty-dolla-sign-for-trust-me|title=Bhad Bhabie Recruits Ty Dolla Sign for \"Trust Me\"|website=Complex|accessdate=June 15, 2018}}</ref> On July 26, she released the video for \"Trust Me\", featuring guest appearances from [[Theo Von]] and [[Bella Thorne]].\n\nOn August 14, 2018, Bregoli announced her upcoming mixtape ''[[15 (mixtape)|15]]''. It would feature guest appearances from Lil Yachty, Ty Dolla $ign, [[YG (rapper)|YG]], [[Lil Baby]], City Girls and Asian Doll. One day later, she received a gold certification from the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] for her single \"Gucci Flip Flops\".\n\nOn August 30, 2018, Bregoli released her new single \"Yung and Bhad\" featuring City Girls.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bhad-bhabie-and-city-girls-are-yung-and-bhad-on-their-new-collab-new-song.1980124.html|title=Bhad Bhabie & City Girls Are \"Yung And Bhad\" On Their New Collab|website=HotNewHipHop|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref> Two days before the release of her debut mixtape, she released a music video for Thot Opps (Clout Drop) and Bout That.{{citation needed|date=November 2018}} On September 18, 2018, she released ''15''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/bhad-bhabie-shares-debut-mixtape-15-listen/|title=Bhad Bhabie Shares Debut Mixtape 15: Listen|work=Pitchfork|last=Blais-Billie|first=Braudie|date=September 18, 2018|accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> She released the single \"Geek'd\" featuring Lil Baby, with a music video released two days later.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Bhad-Bhabie-Releases-Geekd-Video-Featuring-Lil-Baby-20180921|title=Bhad Bhabie Releases 'Geek'd' Video Featuring Lil Baby|last=Desk|first=BWW News|website=BroadwayWorld.com|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Bhad Bhabie|title=BHAD BHABIE \"Geek'd\" feat. Lil Baby (Official Music Video) {{!}} Danielle Bregoli|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=66h5dGoQ1IU|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref> Other album tracks such as \"No More Love\", \"Famous\", \"Count It\" and \"Shhh\" were presented as video shorts on YouTube. On October 17, she released \"Juice\" featuring rapper [[YG (rapper)|YG]]. A music video for \"Juice\" was also released, with a guest appearance from UFC Women's Featherweight Champion [[Cris Cyborg]], but YG did not appear on the video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/10/bhad-bhabie-and-yg-juice-music-video-features-ufc-champ-cris-cyborg|title=Bhad Bhabie's New Music Video for 'Juice' Features UFC Champ Cris Cyborg|website=Complex|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Bhad Bhabie|title=BHAD BHABIE feat. YG \u2013 \"Juice\" (Official Music Video) {{!}} Danielle Bregoli|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EmNwaoaTkiY|accessdate=December 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn November 16, 2018, she embarked on the third and fourth legs of her tour,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bp2zOj1FsRP/|title=Bhad Bhabie promotes tour in Australia and West Coast of US|last=|first=|date=November 6, 2018|website=Instagram|accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref> on the west coast of the US and Australia/New Zealand respectively. The tour received good reviews, stating Bregoli's stage presence made the show, some even comparing her to Britney Spears on the early years of her career.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://tendaily.com.au/views/a181210txn/bhad-bhabies-concert-proves-all-her-haters-wrong-20181211|title=Bhad Bhabie\u00b4s concert proves all her haters wrong.|last=|first=|date=December 11, 2018|work=10daily|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ambientlightblog.com/bhad-bhabie-auckland-nz-2018/|title=Bhad Bhabie, Auckland NZ, 2018|last=|first=|date=December 15, 2018|work=Ambient Light Blog|accessdate=January 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2019&ndash;present: ''Bringing Up Bhabie, Ride or Die'' and hiatus===\n\nIn January 2019, Bregoli released two singles: \"Babyface Savage\" featuring [[Tory Lanez]] and \"Bestie\" featuring [[Kodak Black]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8493059/bhad-bhabie-babyface-savage-video-tory-lanez|title=Bhad Bhabie & Tory Lanez Flex in Neon-Splashed 'Babyface Savage' Video: Watch|last=Saponara|first=Michael|date=January 10, 2019|website=Billboard|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|accessdate=January 11, 2019}}</ref> Babyface Savage gained a lot of traction in YouTube and Twitter especially, with many clips of the songs gaining tens of thousands retweets and likes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/BhadBhabie/status/1083505266279104512|title=Babyface Savage Twitter snippet|last=|first=|date=|website=Twitter.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|accessdate=}}</ref> The song also charted on Canada and on the Bubbling Under Hot 100 in the US, extending her record of the youngest female to have more entries in over 20 years.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tmz.com/2018/05/16/danielle-bregoli-bhad-bhabie-does-not-know-leann-rimes-billboard-chart-history/|title=Danielle Bregoli Matches a LeAnn Rimes Record, Has No Clue Who LeAnn Is|website=TMZ|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> The music video reached 20 million views in under 2 months. Bestie's music video, directed by Michael Garcia, came out February 25, and was praised for its visuals and storyline. It featured product placement by multiple brands, and had a guest appearance by [[DMX (rapper)|DMX]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bfmLYKxJ0UA|title=Bestie Music Video|author=Bhad Bhabie|date=February 25, 2019|website=YouTube|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn the same month, she announced an endorsement deal with Copycat Beauty, where she will promote the brand's products on her social media and music videos.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tmz.com/2019/01/16/danielle-bregoli-bhad-bhabie-makeup-endorsement-deal-copycat/|title=Danielle Bregoli Says Her Makeup Endorsements Could Rival Kylie Jenner's|website=TMZ|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> She reportedly will be making and a percentage of the sales for the six-month deal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/01/bhad-bhabie-scores-900k-makeup-endorsement-deal|title=Bhad Bhabie Scores K Makeup Endorsement Deal|website=Complex|access-date=February 14, 2019}}</ref> The deal was successful, as the company's sales spiked, reaching 500,000 on the first day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tmz.com/2019/01/21/danielle-bregoli-makeup-endorsement-deal-huge-sales-beauty-line-coming/|title=Danielle Bregoli's Makeup Endorsement Deal Already Bringing in Huge Sales|website=TMZ|language=en|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\nBregoli also released the trailer of her new reality show, ''[[Bringing Up Bhabie]]'', which would detail her daily life and her building her music career. The show will come out on [[Snapchat]], as one of their many upcoming Snap Originals. The first season had 12 episodes, and TMZ reported outstanding ratings of over 10 million unique viewers in its first 24 hours. They also reported she was set to make over 10 million dollars during 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tmz.com/2019/02/08/danielle-bregoli-snapchat-show-viewers-bringing-up-bhad-bhabie/|title=DANIELLE BREGOLI \u2013 SNAPCHAT SERIES ON PACE TO SET RECORDS \u2013 ... TV & Movie Roles Next?!?|last=|first=|date=Feb 2019|website=Tmz.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=}}</ref> During September 2019, the reality show was renewed by Snapchat for a second season due to air in Summer 2020.\n\nDuring April and May 2019, Bregoli released a remix of Bestie by Spenda C Nola Bounce and a radio version of the song with [[Megan Thee Stallion]]. She released the version with Megan in order for her song to be played on the radio as radio stations were boycotting Kodak Black at the time. Bregoli also released the double singles \u201cLotta Dem\u201d and her song \u201cSpaz\u201d which features [[YBN Nahmir]]. The making of the Spaz music video was recorded for her Snapchat show \u201cBringing Up Bhabie\u201d.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/bhad-bhabie-lotta-dem-spaz-ybn-nahmir-841707/|title=Bhad Bhabie Is Back for Summer|first1=Claire|last1=Shaffer|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=May 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe following month, she released another single called \u201cGet Like Me\u201d which has a feature from [[NLE Choppa]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Bhad Bhabie and NLE Choppa drop \u201cGet Like Me\u201d |url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/06/26/bhad-bhabie-and-nle-choppa-drop-get-like-me |website=The FADER |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Bhad Bhabie's 'Get Like Me' Feat. NLE Choppa: Watch the Video |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8517909/bhad-bhabie-get-like-me-nle-choppa-video |website=Billboard |accessdate=7 April 2020 |date=27 June 2019}}</ref> On August 22, 2019, she announced the release of her new game \u201cRide or Die\u201d which features Bregoli as an animated character where the player has to get her to run from the police.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Spangler |first1=Todd |title=Bhad Bhabie Joyriding Game \u2018Ride or Die!\u2019 Geared Around Stealing Cars, Outrunning Cops |url=https://variety.com/2019/digital/news/bhad-bhabie-game-ride-or-die-bbtv-1203309629/ |website=Variety |language=en |date=22 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, a video of Bregoli wearing [[box braids]] was posted to [[Instagram]], causing controversy over cultural appropriation. This caused her to go on a social media hiatus.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bhad Bhabie claps back at criticism of box braids hairstyle |url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/12/04/bhad-bhabie-defends-box-braids-hairstyle-accused-cultural-appropriation-11267702/ |website=Metro |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=en |date=4 December 2019}}</ref> In February 2020, she ended her hiatus with a freestyle to [[Nicki Minaj]]\u2019s song \"[[Yikes (Nicki Minaj song)|Yikes]]\",<ref>{{cite web |title=Bhad Bhabie Drops 'Yikes' Freestyle |url=https://www.rap-up.com/2020/02/11/bhad-bhabie-nicki-minaj-yikes-freestyle/ |website=Rap-Up |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> and another song called \u201c$\u201d with [[Lil Gotit]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Zidel |first1=Alex |title=Bhad Bhabie & Lil Gotit Link Up For \"$\" |url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/bhad-bhabie-and-lil-gotit-link-up-for-s-new-song.1986405.html |website=HotNewHipHop |accessdate=7 April 2020 |language=en |date=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n=== Mixtapes ===\n* ''[[15 (mixtape)|15]]'' (2018)\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:200px;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:45px;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/hot-100|title=Billboard Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=September 12, 2017}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:45px;\"| [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B/HH]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/r-b-hip-hop-songs|title=Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:45px;\"| [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br><ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-hot-100|title=Billboard Canadian Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=October 10, 2017}}\n* \"[[15 (mixtape)|Gucci Flip Flop's]]\": {{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-hot-100/2018-05-19|title=Billboard Canadian Hot 100: May 19, 2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 15, 2018}}\n* \"Babyface Savage\": {{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-hot-100/2019-01-26|title=Billboard Canadian Hot 100: January 26, 2019|work=Billboard|accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[These Heaux]]\"\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 2017\n| 77 || 34 || 57\n|\n* [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]: Gold<ref name=\"RIAA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=bhad+bhabie#search_section|title=Gold & Platinum \u2013 RIAA: Bhad Bhabie|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]|accessdate=April 14, 2019}}</ref>\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Hi Bich]]\"\n| 68 || 29 || 66\n|\n* RIAA: Gold<ref name=\"RIAA\"/>\n* [[Music Canada|MC]]: Gold<ref name=\"MC-Cert\">{{cite web|url=https://musiccanada.com/gold-platinum/?_gp_search=bhad%20bhabie|title=Gold/Platinum \u2013 Music Canada|publisher=[[Music Canada]]|accessdate=April 14, 2019}}</ref>\n| ''15''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Whachu Know\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| rowspan=\"4\"{{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"I Got It\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Mama Don't Worry (Still Ain't Dirty)\"\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \u201cBoth of Em\u201d\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2018\n|  \u2014 ||  \u2014 ||  \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Gucci Flip Flops (song)|Gucci Flip Flops]]\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[Lil Yachty]])}}\n| 79<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/lil-yachty/chart-history/bubbling-under-hot-100|title=Lil Yachty Chart History: Bubbling Under Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 22, 2018}}</ref>|| 39 || 62\n|\n* RIAA: Platinum<ref name=\"RIAA\"/>\n* MC: Gold<ref name=\"MC-Cert\"/>\n| rowspan=\"3\"| ''15''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Trust Me\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[Ty Dolla Sign]])}}\n| \u2014 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Trust Me\" 